# SnapTrade-only broker integrations

HappyTrader v2 routes **all** broker connectivity through [SnapTrade](https://snaptrade.com).
Direct broker OAuth (native Schwab, Fidelity API, etc.) is **not** permitted unless this rule
is explicitly amended after a documented exception.

## Policy

1. **One integration path:** `app/snaptrade.py` + `app/snaptrade_normalize.py` +
   `app/snaptrade_sync_cli.py`. No parallel `app/<broker>.py` modules.
2. **Schwab included via SnapTrade.** Schwab users connect through the SnapTrade Connection
   Portal like every other broker. Do not add "Connect Schwab" native OAuth UI or crons.
3. **Exception gate:** A direct integration is allowed only when SnapTrade demonstrably does
   **not** support the broker **and** the operator has signed off in
   `docs/PHASE0_SNAPTRADE_VALIDATION.md` (or a successor validation doc). Document the
   exception in `docs/V2_TENANT_KEY_DESIGN.md` and add a row to the validation checklist.
4. **Tenant key:** Every seed row must carry `tenant_id = "<broker_slug>:<broker_uuid>"`.
   SnapTrade accounts use `broker_slug=snaptrade` and SnapTrade's account UUID verbatim.
   See `docs/V2_TENANT_KEY_DESIGN.md`.

## Before editing broker sync code

Load `~/.cursor/skills/broker-sync-safety/SKILL.md` and walk its pre-flight checklist.

## Forbidden patterns

- New routes under `/schwab/*` or env vars `SCHWAB_APP_KEY` / `SCHWAB_APP_SECRET` in active code paths
- Postgres helpers that read/write `schwab_connections` (table is legacy until Phase 6 drop)
- Minting our own account identifiers (`broker_accounts.id` SERIAL, `(user_id, account_name)` joins)
- UI copy steering Schwab users away from SnapTrade ("SnapTrade doesn't support Schwab")

## Allowed

- CSV manual upload (`app/upload.py`) — no OAuth, display-only `account` label
- Comments / DDL for legacy tables until `scripts/admin/v2_cutover_reset.py` Phase 6 drop
- Historical references in `docs/archive/` and regression tests for **data shape**, not live OAuth

## SnapTrade plan & webhook scope (2026-07-02)

- **Plan is REAL-TIME** (upgraded from Daily/cached). `ACCOUNT_HOLDINGS_UPDATED` now
  fires many times a day; the handler **debounces per account** (`_queue_snaptrade_sync`
  in `app/webhooks.py`, `SNAPTRADE_WEBHOOK_DEBOUNCE_SECONDS` default 60s) because
  reporting is close-based and one dbt build per intraday mark wiggle is wasted CI.
- **The real-time plan is per-broker, NOT universal — Schwab is daily-only via SnapTrade.**
  `snaptrade_sync_observations` proved SnapTrade auto-polls Schwab exactly once/day
  (evening UTC), unchanged before vs after the 2026-07-02 upgrade. The plan governs
  SnapTrade's *automatic* poll cadence; it does nothing for a broker SnapTrade can't
  poll in real-time (same broker list as Trade Detection — Schwab excluded). So
  webhook freshness has a floor = the broker's auto-poll cadence.
- **Intraday freshness for daily-only brokers = force-refresh (BILLED).** The
  market-close cron `happytrader-snaptrade-refresh` (~20:10 UTC weekdays) runs
  `python -m app.snaptrade_sync_cli --force-refresh`, which calls
  `refresh_brokerage_authorization` per account UP FRONT (one settle window), then
  reads + one batched push. This is a **separate, per-call-billed** SnapTrade API —
  being on real-time does NOT make it free. Only the close-time cron force-refreshes;
  the 23:00 UTC `happytrader-snaptrade-sync` cron stays a plain unbilled read backstop.
- **Trade Detection (`TRADE_DETECTION`) is DEFERRED, not built.** SnapTrade's
  `TRADE_DETECTION` feed is only supported for Webull, tastytrade, Alpaca, moomoo —
  **NOT Schwab**, which is the only broker connected today — and is billed as an
  *extra per-account monthly subscription*. Do not build subscription management
  (subscribe/list/cancel) or a `TRADE_DETECTION` webhook branch until a supported
  broker is actually connected and the per-account cost is signed off. Docs:
  https://docs.snaptrade.com/docs/trade-detection
- **Known gap (accepted):** we do NOT consume SnapTrade's `CONNECTION_BROKEN` /
  `CONNECTION_FIXED` webhooks. Broken state is inferred *reactively* during a sync
  attempt (`mark_snaptrade_connection_broken` on an auth error in `app/snaptrade.py`).
  If Trade Detection is ever built, pair it with these connection-health events
  (per SnapTrade guidance) so a subscribed account with a dead connection is
  surfaced instead of silently emitting nothing.

## Verification

When adding a broker-facing surface:

- [ ] Connect flow uses `url_for('snaptrade_connect')` only
- [ ] Sync is webhook-driven (`ACCOUNT_HOLDINGS_UPDATED` → `app/webhooks.py`, debounced per account under the real-time plan); the `happytrader-snaptrade-refresh` cron (~20:10 UTC, `--force-refresh`, billed) forces an intraday repoll for daily-only brokers (Schwab), and `happytrader-snaptrade-sync` (23:00 UTC, unbilled) is the plain missed-delivery backstop (see `app/render.yaml`)
- [ ] Seed writes include `tenant_id` from `get_or_create_broker_tenant`
- [ ] No new imports from deleted `app/schwab.py`
